    {
      "id": "RQ-0002",
      "status": "done",
      "title": "Unify launch-scoped flag handling across reuse guards and open correction",
      "description": "Principles violated: C) DRY, E) Make bugs hard to write, F) Fail fast, J) Consistency/Integrity.\n\nWhy it matters: the wrapper treats launch-scoped behavior inconsistently. `buildExecutionPlan` only blocks `--profile`, `--session-name`, and `--cdp` from silently reusing an already-active implicit session, so other launch-scoped auth/session options like `--state` and `--auto-connect` slip through and get appended after the managed `--session`. Separately, post-open wrong-tab correction only runs for `--profile`, so equivalent fresh-launch paths like `--session-name` never get the same recovery.\n\nMinimal proposed fix: centralize launch-scoped flag classification in one helper and use it everywhere the wrapper makes launch-time decisions: implicit-session reuse blocking, recovery-hint generation, and post-open tab correction. Cover at least `--profile`, `--session-name`, `--cdp`, `--state`, and `--auto-connect`, with explicit comments if any upstream option is intentionally excluded.\n\nAcceptance criteria: `npm test` stays green; active implicit-session calls with `--state` or `--auto-connect` fail with the same structured `sessionMode: \"fresh\"` recovery guidance as the existing startup-scoped flags; fresh `--session-name` opens trigger the same tab-correction path already used for profiled opens.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "correctness",
        "sessions"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/runtime.ts",
        "extensions/agent-browser/index.ts",
        "README.md",
        "docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md",
        "test/agent-browser.test.ts",
        "npx tsx"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: extensions/agent-browser/lib/runtime.ts:12-12 :: `STARTUP_SCOPED_FLAGS` only includes `--cdp`, `--profile`, and `--session-name`.",
        "path: extensions/agent-browser/lib/runtime.ts:705-718 :: only those startup-scoped flags are blocked from reusing an already-active implicit managed session.",
        "path: extensions/agent-browser/index.ts:904-912 :: open-result tab correction only runs when the original args include `--profile`.",
        "workflow: npx tsx <<'EOF' ... buildExecutionPlan(['--state', '/tmp/auth.json', 'open', 'https://example.com'], active managed session) ... EOF :: observed `validationError = null`, `startupScopedFlags = []`, and injected `effectiveArgs = ['--json','--session','piab-demo-123','--state', ...]`.",
        "workflow: npx tsx <<'EOF' ... buildExecutionPlan(['--auto-connect', 'open', 'https://example.com'], active managed session) ... EOF :: observed `validationError = null`, `startupScopedFlags = []`, and injected `effectiveArgs = ['--json','--session','piab-demo-123','--auto-connect', ...]`.",
        "workflow: npx tsx <<'EOF' ... fake `--session-name saved-auth open https://example.com` with `sessionMode: 'fresh'` ... EOF :: observed exactly one upstream open invocation and no `tab list` follow-up correction, unlike the profiled open path."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Extract a single source of truth for launch-scoped upstream flags and document why each flag is classified that way.",
        "Reuse that classification in implicit-session validation, recovery-hint generation, and post-open wrong-tab correction.",
        "Add regressions for `--state`, `--auto-connect`, and `--session-name` fresh-open correction alongside the existing `--profile` coverage.",
        "Verify by running `npm test` and confirming the new launch-scoped cases either fail fast with `sessionMode: \"fresh\"` guidance or execute the expected `tab list` correction path."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "scan: edge cases and bugs in the pi native agent_browser integration and agent-browser passthrough",
