    {
      "id": "RQ-0007",
      "status": "done",
      "title": "Limit inline image attachments to trusted screenshot outputs",
      "description": "Principles violated: E) Make bugs hard to write, G) Least astonishment, I) Security baseline, J) Consistency/Integrity.\n\nWhy it matters: arbitrary page-controlled results are currently reinterpreted as local image paths and attached back into the tool response. That creates a local file disclosure path for commands like `eval` and `get text` when their result happens to be `foo.png` or an absolute `...jpg` path, and it also turns benign text like `notes.png` into misleading attachment failures.\n\nMinimal proposed fix: only resolve and attach local images for commands that are explicitly expected to create screenshot-style image artifacts, such as `screenshot` and trusted structured screenshot results inside batch flows. Treat plain strings and generic `{ path }` payloads from other commands as text unless the command contract explicitly guarantees a local image file.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "security",
        "correctness",
        "results"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/presentation.ts",
        "test/agent-browser.test.ts",
        "npx tsx"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/presentation.ts:539-549 :: `extractImagePath` treats any top-level string or any record with a `path` string ending in an image extension as a local image candidate, regardless of command type.",
        "path: extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/presentation.ts:551-577 :: `attachInlineImage` immediately stats and reads that resolved local path, then appends the image bytes into the tool content.",
        "repro: `npx tsx <<'EOF' ... buildToolPresentation({ commandInfo: { command: 'eval', subcommand: '--stdin' }, cwd: tempDir, envelope: { success: true, data: 'secret.png' } }) ... EOF` :: expected plain text result `secret.png` :: actual `contentTypes: [\"text\",\"image\"]` and `imagePath` pointing at the local temp file.",
        "repro: `npx tsx <<'EOF' ... buildToolPresentation({ commandInfo: { command: 'get', subcommand: 'text' }, cwd: repoRoot, envelope: { success: true, data: absoluteTempImagePath } }) ... EOF` :: expected plain text path echo :: actual inline image attachment from the absolute local file path."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Narrow image attachment detection so it only runs for trusted screenshot-producing commands or explicitly marked screenshot result payloads.",
        "Keep screenshot and batch screenshot attachments working while preventing generic text and eval/get payloads from being resolved as local files.",
        "Add regressions for plain string image-like outputs, absolute image-path strings, and the real screenshot path so the intended behavior is explicit.",
        "Verify by running `npm test` and confirming non-screenshot string/path results stay text-only while screenshot outputs still attach inline images."
      ],
      "notes": [],
